### Key Features

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Multi-Provider** | Unified interface for Binance Futures and Deribit |
| **Order Management** | Place, modify, cancel, and track orders |
| **Position Tracking** | Real-time position monitoring with P&L |
| **WebSocket Streams** | Low-latency market data and user events |
| **Event-Driven** | Async event architecture for fills, updates |
| **Result Pattern** | Type-safe error handling|
| **Secure Auth** | HMAC-SHA256 (Binance) and Ed25519 (Deribit) |
| **100% Tested** | 70+ scenarios, 100% pass rate |
| **TypeScript-First** | Full type definitions with IntelliSense |
| **Testnet Support** | Built-in testnet URLs for development |

### Installation

```bash
npm install ark-alliance-trading-providers-lib
```

### Quick Start

```typescript
import { BinanceRestClient } from 'ark-alliance-trading-providers-lib/Binance';

// Initialize client
const client = new BinanceRestClient(apiKey, secret, { testnet: true });

// Place order with type-safe Result pattern
const orderResult = await client.placeOrder({
  symbol: 'BTCUSDT',
  side: 'BUY',
  type: 'MARKET',
  quantity: 0.001
});

if (orderResult.success) {
  console.log(`Order placed! ID: ${orderResult.data.orderId}`);
} else {
  console.error(`Error: ${orderResult.error.message}`);
}
```

## Functional Use Cases

### 1. Algorithmic Trading Bot

**Scenario**: Automated trading strategy execution

**Workflow**:
```typescript
import { BinanceRestClient, BinanceWebSocketClient } from 'ark-alliance-trading-providers-lib';

// Initialize clients
const rest = new BinanceRestClient(apiKey, secret, { testnet: true });
const ws = new BinanceWebSocketClient({ testnet: true });

// Subscribe to market data
ws.subscribeBookTicker('BTCUSDT');
ws.on('bookTicker', async (ticker) => {
  const signal = analyzeMarket(ticker);

  if (signal === 'BUY') {
    const result = await rest.placeOrder({
      symbol: 'BTCUSDT',
      side: 'BUY',
      type: 'MARKET',
      quantity: 0.001
    });

    if (result.success) {
      console.log(`Buy order placed: ${result.data.orderId}`);
    }
  }
});
```

### 2. Portfolio Management

```typescript
class PortfolioManager {
  async getTotalBalance(): Promise<number> {
    const binancePositions = await this.binanceClient.getPositionRisk();
    const deribitPositions = await this.deribitClient.getPositions();

    return this.calculateTotalValue([
      ...binancePositions.data || [],
      ...deribitPositions.data || []
    ]);
  }
}
```
